<p>Using <code>lambda</code> syntax allows to use only one
expression-style value for function definition (i.e. no multiple
statements). The following two expressions are equivalent:</p>

<pre>def f1(): return <b>...</b></pre>
<pre>f1 = lambda: <b>...</b></pre>

<p>That is, <code>lambda</code> syntax implies invisible
<code>return</code> statement.</p>

<p>Full-fledged <code>def</code> syntax is more powerful, but requires
one to give function a name (technically, bind the function to a
variable).</p>
